# Fix builds before finishing

**Before considering a task complete**, run the project’s build (e.g. `npm run build`) and fix any failures.

- Fix build errors **even if they are unrelated** to the changes you just made (e.g. a pre-existing config bug or a prior change).
- Do not leave the repo in a broken-build state.
- If the build was already failing when you started, still resolve it before finishing, unless the user explicitly says otherwise.

This keeps the project in a shippable state and avoids broken builds piling up.
